Ngoc Minh Nguyen is an Intern AI Engineer with 3 months of commercial internship experience. Their core expertise lies in designing and implementing advanced AI systems, particularly focusing on Large Language Models (LLMs), Multi-agent systems, and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). They have practical experience in fine-tuning LLMs like LLaMA 3, Mistral, and Phi-4 using QLoRA via Unsloth, achieving high evaluation scores (e.g., BERTScore F1 = 0.8913, ROUGE > 0.7) and mitigating hallucination risks through retrieval optimization and reranking. Their work includes developing AI-powered websites with LangChain and FastAPI, integrating natural language interfaces, and building sophisticated multi-agent systems that leverage reasoning-driven tool-use, memory retention, context-aware conversations, and response verification mechanisms. Additionally, they possess foundational knowledge in Computer Vision and Digital Image Processing, demonstrated through projects utilizing OpenCV for vision solutions.
Technically, Ngoc Minh is proficient in Python and Java, with extensive hands-on experience across a robust AI/ML stack including Langchain, Pytorch, Langgraph, Hugging Face, Unsloth, Cleanlab, OpenCV, Scikit-learn, Pandas, Chainlit, Gradio, and FastAPI for backend development. They are adept with databases such as MongoDB and SQLite, and possess foundational knowledge in cloud platforms like AWS and containerization with Docker. Version control is managed using Git. Their domain knowledge spans Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, and Data Structures and Algorithms, with a strong emphasis on end-to-end AI system design, agentic AI, and human-in-the-loop methodologies for building robust and context-aware conversational AI applications.